Attributes.description: Introductory course in mostly non-algorithmic topics including: planarity and Kuratowski's theorem, graph colouring, graph minors, random graphs, cycles in graphs, Ramsey theory, extremal graph theory. Proofs emphasized. Intended for Honours students.
Attributes.prereq: Pre-reqs: A score of 68% or higher in one of MATH 220, MATH 223, MATH 226, CPSC 121. (And 6 credits of MATH numbered 300 or above.)
Attributes.date_buildings: Term: 2, Days: Mon Wed Fri, Start Time: 15:00, End Time: 16:00, Building: Mathematics, Room: 204
